.TH "efi_parse_options" 9 "efi_parse_options" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
efi_parse_options \- Parse EFI command line options
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "efi_status_t" efi_parse_options
.BI "(char const *cmdline "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cmdline" 12
kernel command line
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Parse the ASCII string \fIcmdline\fP for EFI options, denoted by the efi=
option, e.g. efi=nochunk.

It should be noted that efi= is parsed in two very different
environments, first in the early boot environment of the EFI boot
stub, and subsequently during the kernel boot.
.SH "RETURN"
status code
